30namespace webrtc {
31
32class SuppressionGain {
33 public:
34 SuppressionGain(const EchoCanceller3Config& config,
35 Aec3Optimization optimization,
36 int sample_rate_hz,
37 size_t num_capture_channels);
38 ~SuppressionGain();
39 void GetGain(
40 rtc::ArrayView<const std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>>
41 nearend_spectrum,
42 rtc::ArrayView<const std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>> echo_spectrum,
43 rtc::ArrayView<const std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>>
44 residual_echo_spectrum,
45 rtc::ArrayView<const std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>>
46 comfort_noise_spectrum,
47 const RenderSignalAnalyzer& render_signal_analyzer,
48 const AecState& aec_state,
49 const std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>& render,
50 bool clock_drift,
51 float* high_bands_gain,
52 std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>* low_band_gain);
53
54 bool IsDominantNearend() {
55 return dominant_nearend_detector_->IsNearendState();
56 }
57
58 // Toggles the usage of the initial state.
59 void SetInitialState(bool state);
60
61 private:
62 // Computes the gain to apply for the bands beyond the first band.
63 float UpperBandsGain(
64 rtc::ArrayView<const std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>> echo_spectrum,
65 rtc::ArrayView<const std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>>
66 comfort_noise_spectrum,
67 const absl::optional<int>& narrow_peak_band,
68 bool saturated_echo,
69 const std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>& render,
70 const std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>& low_band_gain) const;
71
72 void GainToNoAudibleEcho(const std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>& nearend,
73 const std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>& echo,
74 const std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>& masker,
75 std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>* gain) const;
76
77 void LowerBandGain(
78 bool stationary_with_low_power,
79 const AecState& aec_state,
80 rtc::ArrayView<const std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>>
81 suppressor_input,
82 rtc::ArrayView<const std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>> residual_echo,
83 rtc::ArrayView<const std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>> comfort_noise,
84 bool clock_drift,
85 std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>* gain);
86
87 void GetMinGain(rtc::ArrayView<const float> weighted_residual_echo,
88 rtc::ArrayView<const float> last_nearend,
89 rtc::ArrayView<const float> last_echo,
90 bool low_noise_render,
91 bool saturated_echo,
92 rtc::ArrayView<float> min_gain) const;
93
94 void GetMaxGain(rtc::ArrayView<float> max_gain) const;
95
96 class LowNoiseRenderDetector {
97 public:
98 bool Detect(const std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>& render);
99
100 private:
101 float average_power_ = 32768.f * 32768.f;
102 };
103
104 struct GainParameters {
105 explicit GainParameters(
106 const EchoCanceller3Config::Suppressor::Tuning& tuning);
107 const float max_inc_factor;
108 const float max_dec_factor_lf;
109 std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1> enr_transparent_;
110 std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1> enr_suppress_;
111 std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1> emr_transparent_;
112 };
113
114 static int instance_count_;
115 std::unique_ptr<ApmDataDumper> data_dumper_;
116 const Aec3Optimization optimization_;
117 const EchoCanceller3Config config_;
118 const size_t num_capture_channels_;
119 const int state_change_duration_blocks_;
120 std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1> last_gain_;
121 std::vector<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>> last_nearend_;
122 std::vector<std::array<float, kFftLengthBy2Plus1>> last_echo_;
123 LowNoiseRenderDetector low_render_detector_;
124 bool initial_state_ = true;
125 int initial_state_change_counter_ = 0;
126 std::vector<aec3::MovingAverage> nearend_smoothers_;
127 const GainParameters nearend_params_;
128 const GainParameters normal_params_;
129 std::unique_ptr<NearendDetector> dominant_nearend_detector_;
130
131 RTC_DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(SuppressionGain);
132};
133
134} // namespace webrtc
